Trying to decide about micro.blog. Mine is currently [[here|https://micro.alexjj.com]]. Arguably this site would disappear into micro.blog as I could do daily posts and also the apps, and webUI etc. all make it very easy to add an entry to it. That's one of the main reasons why I keep this site. This site does have the wiki nature about it though....although I find I use that less and less for some reason. 

Micro.blog theming is all built on Hugo, yet it feels more complex than a regular Hugo site to build. It probably doesn't help that I've not made a Hugo site in ages and have since forgotten. I'm trying to use a stock theme but I'm struggling. For now it's the Arabica theme with a few `display: none` in the custom CSS to hide a couple of things for the time being. I would really like a lot of things changed but it's quite a big time commitment to make a new theme. Logic dictates I should use it first to establish that I like it, then come back and theme it.

