I'm hesitant to go all in until I do a custom theme...perhaps overkill...I also like the idea of a landing page so I can change everything else around. However, I find them annoying so hmm... I also like the idea of my blog being called fondoftea, and so having the same domain makes more sense. If I'm microblogging all the way then combining these daily posts into it make sense that it takes over the root domain (whichever one). 

I'm talking myself out of a Tiddlywiki but maybe having one still makes sense for random stuff. It's good to look things up in, although when do I do that and when do I add anything? I'm even thinking about dokuwiki instead. (I like the forced structure a regular wiki gives). Or maybe something weird like a GitHub repo wiki...

Micro.blog does tick a lot of boxes and is pretty comprehensive across all the areas I like - short posts, long posts, photos, having phone apps, a webUI, an option for it all to be managed by someone else. I could even break into newsletters and podcasts üòÖ (Sorry world)